The Queen's son and daughter-in-law Prince Edward and Sophie, Countess of Wessex are touring Antigua and Barbuda, St Lucia, and St Vincent and the Grenadines this week to celebrate the Queen's Platinum Jubilee. After touching down in St Lucia on Friday, April 22, Sophie and Edward have had a busy royal schedule meeting local residents and politicians in St Lucia and St Vincent and the Grenadines. On Monday, the Wessexes were due to travel to Antigua and Barbuda.